Since you mentioned Turing, you would recall that the way Alan Turing broke Enigma was by providing Bombe(the actual decrypting machine) some initial references of the codes. Part of the code was manually decoded and then that data was used to decode the rest of the message. There was always human assistance.

It’s not a surprise there is still a major human element to this, but I am curious from those responses if it’s just M or human not a hybrid, e.g if M can’t parse it, it relies on a complete human response, rather than M being able to be directed and to then complete the response.
